"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-surfing-tahiti-paris-olympics-why\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Sometimes, the unwieldy nature of the Olympics forces events to be held\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094gasp!\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094outside the host city.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 104, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Soccer, for instance, is usually scattered around the host country\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094the Paris Olympics will include matches in Bordeaux, Marseille, Nantes and other cities.\", \"from\": 106, \"to\": 263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 218, \"end\": 226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux\", \"score\": 0.9999999717138057, \"rank\": 2.8214808428174797e-08, \"text\": \"Bordeaux\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux\"}, {\"begin\": 228, \"end\": 237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.9993502049705699, \"rank\": 0.0006502175289549988, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}, {\"begin\": 239, \"end\": 245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nantes\", \"score\": 0.9921811321111899, \"rank\": 0.007880484319940834, \"text\": \"Nantes\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nantes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nantes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Los Angeles Olympics in 2028 will includeeventsin Oklahoma City.\", \"from\": 264, \"to\": 332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 268, \"end\": 288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1932_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8741560102915605, \"rank\": 0.1439605610749293, \"text\": \"Los Angeles Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1932_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1932_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 318, \"end\": 326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma\", \"score\": 0.941209377803761, \"rank\": 0.06173054042807619, \"text\": \"Oklahoma\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Heck, the 2026 Winter Olympics will have two host cities\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094Milan and Cortina d'Ampezzo, Italy.\", \"from\": 333, \"to\": 427, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And then there is a situation like surfing at the 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 429, \"to\": 493, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The competition will be held 9,765 miles away from Paris in Teahupo'o\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094a village on the island of Tahiti in French Polynesia.\", \"from\": 494, \"to\": 620, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 545, \"end\": 550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999994311111, \"rank\": 5.690865059683038e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 593, \"end\": 599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999312055296625, \"rank\": 6.879920352451911e-05, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 610, \"end\": 619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9891725515152686, \"rank\": 0.010945965359503398, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us delve into why this is the case, which American celebrity will be making the trip to Teahupo'o, and whether anything like this has happened before.\", \"from\": 622, \"to\": 776, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 668, \"end\": 676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999970718860945, \"rank\": 1.6675349586503679e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Five sites under French jurisdiction applied to host Olympic surfing: Biarritz, Lacanau, Les Landes, La Torche and Teahupo\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099o.\", \"from\": 778, \"to\": 905, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 795, \"end\": 801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.5016155286493693, \"rank\": 0.7883596258894423, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All but Teahupo\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099o are in France proper, and all those in France proper but La Torche are in the southwest of the country specifically.\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 1042, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 933, \"end\": 939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9984538995590979, \"rank\": 0.001546623911519108, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 965, \"end\": 971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9984538995590979, \"rank\": 0.001546623911519108, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 986, \"end\": 992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torche_(band)\", \"score\": 0.9906142217458151, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Torche\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torche_(band)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torche_(band)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Teahupo\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099o won the right to host the competition just before the pandemic, with the International Olympic Committeecitingwidespread support from the surfing community.\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1212, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The village currently hosts astopon the World Surf League's annual tour, and French Polynesian surfers usually compete under their own flag outside Olympic auspices (rather than the French flag).\", \"from\": 1213, \"to\": 1408, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1253, \"end\": 1270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Surf_League\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.340729979330226e-17, \"text\": \"World Surf League\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Surf_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Surf_League\"}, {\"begin\": 1290, \"end\": 1296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.5016155286493693, \"rank\": 0.7883596258894423, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1297, \"end\": 1307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesian_culture\", \"score\": 0.9999622367704482, \"rank\": 3.4127907520727506e-05, \"text\": \"Polynesian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesian_culture\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesian_culture\"}, {\"begin\": 1395, \"end\": 1406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jost is an avid surfer, as he discussed in his 2020memoir,A Very Punchable Face.\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1490, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Accordingly, NBC sent him to Tahiti to help out play-by-play announcer Joe Turpel and analyst Michael Parsons.\", \"from\": 1491, \"to\": 1601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1504, \"end\": 1507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999987894373641, \"rank\": 1.0567587804120552e-06, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 1520, \"end\": 1526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999312055296625, \"rank\": 6.879920352451911e-05, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 1585, \"end\": 1600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Parsons_(figure_skater)\", \"score\": 0.5920354775093549, \"rank\": 0.5378151260502823, \"text\": \"Michael Parsons\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Parsons_(figure_skater)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Parsons_(figure_skater)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m honored to get to watch the best surfers in the world compete on one of the heaviest waves imaginable, and to help showcase the rich history of surfing in Tahiti,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Jost said in a June 26 network release, adding: \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAnd my Writer\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Guild health insurance is excited to see what the coral reef does to my back.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Yes!\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1767, \"end\": 1773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999312055296625, \"rank\": 6.879920352451911e-05, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 1778, \"end\": 1782, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Jost\", \"score\": 0.9884917653236303, \"rank\": 0.011582985132046792, \"text\": \"Jost\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Jost\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Jost\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1956, the Summer Olympics were held in Melbourne.\", \"from\": 1934, \"to\": 1986, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1976, \"end\": 1985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"score\": 0.9999993500730235, \"rank\": 3.473167035510178e-07, \"text\": \"Melbourne\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Due to Australia's strict equine quarantine policies, equestrian events for the Games wereheldin Stockholm\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00949,687 miles away.\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2113, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1994, \"end\": 2003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.99999897206506, \"rank\": 1.0275005979239601e-06, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 2041, \"end\": 2051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.999912515312499, \"rank\": 7.907517112997048e-05, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 2115, \"to\": 2141, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Patrick Andres is a staff writer on the Breaking and Trending News team at Sports Illustrated.\", \"from\": 2142, \"to\": 2300, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2206, \"end\": 2213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\", \"score\": 0.9649890255336165, \"rank\": 0.036114121910702714, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://db